From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: conda-forge <conda-forge@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix generate_plugins crash during cross-compilation

During cross-compilation, Pathname.new may fail because the target
architecture's pathname.so extension cannot be loaded by the build
Ruby. This causes an ArgumentError that is caught, but the rescue
handler crashes on latest.name when latest is nil.

Fix both issues: handle nil latest in rescue, and gracefully skip
plugin generation when it fails due to incompatible extensions.

diff --git a/lib/rubygems/installer.rb b/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
--- a/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
+++ b/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
@@ -478,7 +478,9 @@ class Gem::Installer
       regenerate_plugins_for(spec, @plugins_dir)
     end
   rescue ArgumentError => e
-    raise e, "#{latest.name} #{latest.version} #{spec.name} #{spec.version}: #{e.message}"
+    raise e, "#{latest&.name} #{latest&.version} #{spec.name} #{spec.version}: #{e.message}"
+  rescue StandardError
+    nil
   end

